check if patterns in A1 match those in A2

Source: R/utils.R
check_overlap.Rd

check if patterns in A1 match those in A2

check_overlap(A1, A2)

Arguments

A1

a binary matrix
A2

a binary matrix with the same dimensions as A1

Value

a list of three variables

  • among1 a binary vector of each row of A1 identical to some row(s) of A2

  • among2 same as among1 but switch A1 and A2.

  • overlap a binary vector

Examples


check_overlap(matrix(c(1,1,0, 1,0,0),nrow=2,byrow=TRUE),
matrix(c(1,0,1, 1,1,0),nrow=2,byrow=TRUE))
#> $among1
#> [1] 1 0
#> 
#> $among2
#> [1] 0 1
#> 
#> $overlap
#> [1] 0 0
#>
